(7363, 272, 'main_publications', 'mackiewicz p, bodył a, moszczyński k. 2013. the case of horizontal gene transfer from bacteria to the peculiar dinoflagellate plastid genome. mob genet elements. 1;3(4):e25845. [<a title="The case of horizontal gene transfer from bacteria to the peculiar dinoflagellate plastid genome" href="http://grafika.swps.pl/media/km_The_case_of_horizontal_gene_transfer_from_bacteria_to_the_peculiar_dinoflagellate_plastid_genome.pdf">pdf</a>]\r\n\r\nmoszczynski k., mackiewicz p., bodyl a. 2012. evidence for horizontal gene transfer from bacteroidetes bacteria to dinoflagellate minicircles. mol. biol. evol. 29(3), str. 887-892. [<a title="Evidence for Horizontal Gene Transfer from Bacteroidetes Bacteria to Dinoflagellate Minicircles" href="http://grafika.swps.pl/media/km_Evidence_for_Horizontal_Gene_Transfer_from_Bacteroidetes_Bacteria_to_Dinoflagellate_Minicircles.pdf">pdf</a>]\r\n\r\nmoszczynski k., mackiewicz p., bodyl a. 2007. phylogenetic and structural analyses of the peculiar plastid genome of adenoides eludens (dinoflagellata). 10th international colloquium on endocytobiology and symbiosis, september 10­-13, 2007, gmunden, upper austria, book of abstracts: 42. [<a title="Phylogenetic and structural analyses of the peculiar plastid genome of Adenoides eludens (dinoflagellata)" href="http://grafika.swps.pl/media/km_phylogenetic_and_structural_analyses_of_the_peculiar_plastid_genome_of_Adenoides_eludens.pdf">pdf</a>]\r\n\r\nbodył a., moszczyński k. 2006. did the peridinin plastid evolve through tertiary endosymbiosis? a hypothesis, eur. j. phycol. 41, str. 435–448. [<a title="Did the peridinin plastid evolve through tertiary endosymbiosis? A hypothesis" href="http://grafika.swps.pl/media/km_Did_the_peridinin_plastid_evolve_through_tertiary_endosymbiosis.pdf">pdf</a>]'),
